article.headline: President Trump going to Walter Reed after COVID-19 diagnosis
article.body: President Trump is going to Walter Reed Medical Center in nearly Bethesda, Md. for "the next few days" for further evaluation after being diagnosed with COVID-19, the White House said late Friday afternoon. He was being flown by helicopter in what spokeswoman Kayleigh McEnany described as a cautionary measure. She said the president remained in "good spirits." Trump announced early Friday that he had contracted the virus along with his wife, Melania. His doctor said the president was showing "mild" symptoms and was feeling 'fatigued." His wife appeared to be doing better.
